## Developer Guide

If you are new to using `nbdev` here are some useful pointers to get you
started.

### Install Scientist_Experiment_Optimization in Development mode

``` sh
# make sure Scientist_Experiment_Optimization package is installed in development mode
$ pip install -e .

# make changes under nbs/ directory
# ...

# compile to have changes apply to Scientist_Experiment_Optimization
$ nbdev_prepare
```

## Usage

### Installation

Install latest from the GitHub
[repository](https://github.com/2catycm/Scientist-Experiment-Optimization):

``` sh
$ pip install git+https://github.com/2catycm/Scientist-Experiment-Optimization.git
```

or from
[conda](https://anaconda.org/2catycm/Scientist-Experiment-Optimization)

``` sh
$ conda install -c 2catycm Scientist_Experiment_Optimization
```

or from
[pypi](https://pypi.org/project/Scientist-Experiment-Optimization/)

``` sh
$ pip install Scientist_Experiment_Optimization
```
